  "prompt": "What are the full forms of HDFC & ICICI?",
  "response": "HDFC and ICICI are two of India's leading financial institutions. Here are their full forms:\n\n1. **HDFC**: **Housing Development Finance Corporation**\n   - **HDFC Limited** is one of India's premier housing finance institutions. Established in 1977, it specializes in providing housing loans, and it has expanded its services to include banking, life and general insurance, asset management, and more through its subsidiaries.\n\n2. **ICICI**: **Industrial Credit and Investment Corporation of India**\n   - **ICICI Limited** was originally established in 1955 as the Industrial Credit and Investment Corporation of India. It was created to provide project financing to Indian businesses. Over the years, ICICI has evolved into a diversified financial services company, offering a wide range of services including banking, insurance, asset management, and investment banking. The banking arm is known as **ICICI Bank**.\n\nBoth HDFC and ICICI play significant roles in India's financial landscape, offering a variety of services to individuals, businesses, and institutions.",
